{"questionId":"22158787","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Roma decides to test the model. They charge the phone from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> and record the charge of the phone for different values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>. The results are shown in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c6cd4c7527e73a03c4540742129ceb9d2727b454.png\" width=\"542\" height=\"66\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Accept a valid argument in favour of model <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> or against the quadratic model.</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1<br></strong></em><br><em>e.g. any one of the following:</em><br>quadratic has no asymptote<br>quadratic will begin to go down<br>quadratic will become negative<br>quadratic might not go through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br>model <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> is the manufacturer’s model</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22158787","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.12cii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"P=100-100×2-t.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
